  {
    "title": "EU Election Observation Mission Meets with Opposition Chief Whip Dhaka, April 28...",
    "description": "EU Election Observation Mission Meets with Opposition Chief Whip Dhaka, April 28, 2026 (Tuesday): A high-level delegation from the European Union (EU) Election Observation Mission paid a courtesy call on Md. Nahid Islam, Convener of the National Citizen Party (NCP) and Chief Whip of the Opposition, at his office in the Bangladesh National Parliament Building. The EU delegation was led by Ivars Ijabs, Head of the EU Election Observation Mission. Other members of the delegation included Deputy Head Ms. Baiba Zarina, Deputy Chief Observer Ms. Inta Lase, Legal Analyst Ms. Irini Maria Gounari, and Mr. Ryan Islam. The meeting was held in a warm and cordial atmosphere. During the discussion, the EU delegation formally handed over its comprehensive observation report on Bangladesh\u2019s most recent parliamentary election to the Opposition Chief Whip. A key point of discussion at the meeting was the July Charter, with the EU delegation seeking updates on the progress of its implementation. In response, Opposition Chief Whip and NCP Convener Nahid Islam expressed concern over what he described as the government's failure to uphold its commitments to the nation. He added that the National Citizen Party (NCP) remains committed to fighting both within and beyond parliament to uphold the institutional and structural reforms sought during the July uprising. NCP Joint Convener and Member of Parliament for Narayanganj-4, Advocate Abdullah Al Amin, and NCP Joint Member Secretary Alauddin Mohammad were also present at the meeting. (Admin)",
